Sean Patrick Duffy (born October 3, 1971) is an American politician, prosecutor, former sports commentator, and personality. He is a CNN contributor.
He was a cast member on ', 1998's ', and 2002's ', before going on to serve as district attorney of Ashland County, Wisconsin.
He was the U.S. Representative for. He is a member of the Republican Party and supported Donald Trump's 2016 presidential bid.
Duffy resigned from Congress effective September 23, 2019.
